a Loire, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Vergy","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Herefordshire): nickname from Middle English <i>verrei</i>, <i>verie</i> ‘true; reliable, trustworthy’ (Old French <i>verai</i>).","Irish: variant of <b>McVerry</b>, a shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Fearadhaigh</b>, itself an unlenited and subsequently voiced variant of <b>Mac Fhearadhaigh</b>, ‘son of <i>Fearadhach</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘manly’. Compare   McAree   and   McCary  ; also the surnames   Ferry   and   Farry  , from <i>Ó Fearadhaigh</i>.","History: The widow Bridget Very settled with her children in Salem, MA, <i>c.</i> 1634. She had many prominent descendants, including the poet Jones Very (1813–1880)."],"variants":[{"name":"McAree","meanings":["Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Fhearadhaigh</b> ‘son of <i>Fearadhach</i>’, a personal name meaning ‘manly’ (from <i>fear</i> ‘man’). Pronunciation of this name as <i>McAree</i> led to misinterpretation as <i>Mac an Rí</i> ‘son of the king’ and thus to ‘translation’ as   King  . See   McGarry  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Armenbourge Vergy was born in 1002, in Loire, Rhône-Alpes, France, her father, Duke  de Vergy, was 43 and her mother, Elizabeth de Chalon*, was 44. She married Robert Brochard Seigneur de Château-du-Loir in 1029, in Château, Saône-et-Loire, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 22 November 1060, in France, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1002–22 November 1060":"1002–22. november 1060","1002–1060":"1002–1060","1010–1067":"1010–1067","1030–1095":"1030–1095","0960–1023":"0960–1023","0958–1016":"0958–1016","1010":"1010","1030":"1030","1095":"1095","Dec 1016":"detsember 1016","1060":"1060","1029":"1029","22 November 1060":"22. november 1060","bef 975":"0975","1016":"1016","0960":"0960","1002":"1002","1023":"1023","1067":"1067","0958":"0958","Eure, Loire, Rhone-Alpes, 